  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Community-based Nutrition Integrated Programme (CNIP)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">RI incorporated nutrition education components that encourage and support improved  child care practices which aim to prevent acute malnutrition prevalence in affected communities. RI remains one of the main service providers to IDPs and vulnerable communities in both health and nutrition in Zamzam. By partnering with WFP, RI hopes to increase micronutrients intake through home fortification of MNPs. Eventually, this intervention will compliment the ongoing efforts of health and nutrition intervention through the targeting of moderate malnourished children and PLWs thus contributing to reduction of mortality and morbidity cases.  All the beneficiaries receive medical assessment and follow-up every time they visit the facility. Health education sessions that are held before distributing rations include topics such as hygiene promotion, balance diet, immunization, breastfeed, etc. he focus topics will be: hygiene promotion, balanced diet, immunization, breastfeeding, better weaning practices and need to complete the nutrition treatment course among others.</narrative>
  </description>
